...As for Vega, you know... she drinks a lot of water while

\SE[90]Ugh... Someone noisy came early in the morning...

\SE[54]Uwah... Isn't that a bit much...?! \SE[7]I-I have
some good news, so if you could be gentle with me...!

\SE[11]Listen and be amazed! \!\SE[15]I've obtained
information about a new doctor!
\SE[62]Half anticipation, half... or rather, half anxiety.

\SE[7]When you rely too much on something and it doesn't
come true, it can be painful...

\SE[14]This time it's a little different! \!\SE[11]After
all, it's about witches...!

\SE[74]Witches... It's a word from the past. \SE[75]In an
era where magic hasn't been widely popularized... There were
suddenly people who could use magic as if it were a
mutation.

\SE[2]That... is very convenient, isn't it? \SE[3]To be born
with such a privilege only for oneself.

\SE\SE[75]Actually, it must have been convenient.
\!\SE[74]But, it wasn't that easy. \!\SE[75]People were
still wary of the unknown. \.In some places, there were even
places that rejected witches.

\SE[4]Well... it's scary, isn't it? If there were clearly
someone superior to oneself. \SE[16]You might end up
thinking, Let's do it before we get done in!

\SE[74]It became like that, right? The lineage of witches
has been persecuted... \SE[75]You can understand even
without saying more, right?

\SE[74]And then, as the times changed, magic became more
widespread... \SE[75] Witches transformed into magicians.

\SE\SE[74]In that sense, the achievement of the Magic
Academy is significant. \SE[3]At least in terms of general
awareness among people... \SE[74]By eliminating the fear of
the unknown, we were able to eliminate one form of
discrimination.

\SE[66]Hey, I've talked too much about unnecessary things...
\!\SE[3]So, what about those witches then?

\SE[2]This time, the witches are not meant to have any
discriminatory meaning. \SE[3]They are located further north
of Caudine...

\SE[4]One day, it seems that a doctor who can cure anything
suddenly appeared. \SE[2]It goes beyond common sense and is
called a witch....

\SE[90]North of Caudine.... It's incredibly far, isn't it?
\SE[75]The risk of it being a wasted trip is quite high.

\SE[12]On that point, well...\.However! \SE[15]As for me, I
will disclose all the information I have gathered!

\SE[2]Good morning, Laura. \SE[3]I was just thinking about
our strategy now...

\SE\SE[5]Yeah, I heard you. \!\SE[5]We're going to meet the
witch, right?

\SE[74]Your opinion... \!\SE[59]Hmm... It doesn't seem worth
listening to.

\SE[2]I've already made up my mind. \!\SE[1]Let's depart
right away.
\SE[58]...I knew it. Everything would turn out like this...

\SE[74]Vita.... \.I'm sorry to burden you again....
\!\SE[3]Can I leave it to you while I'm away...?

\SE\SE[0]Yes, please don't worry about it. \SE[0]I've never
once thought of taking care of Lunaroa-sama as a burden in
these past three years. \SE[16]Even though I can't fight, I
feel like I can be of some use...

\SE[0]So please depart without worrying. \!\SE[1]I will be
here, waiting for good news. \!\SE[15]...together with
Lunaroa-sama.

\SE[72]It seems like I underestimated you. \!\SE[7]In that
case, I can leave things to you without hesitation.

\SE\SE[15]First, let's aim for Codain! \!\SE[15]We have
already secured a base on site, so let's prepare ourselves
there and launch the attack...!

\SE[16]Huh, you've already made arrangements to that
extent...? \.I'm starting to get a little scared of Cat....

\SE[16]Yes!! \SE[0]I knew Laura-san would answer
immediately. I believed in her determination...!

\SE[12]That was close! \!\SE[38]If you had canceled, I would
have been burdened with a considerable debt in cancellation
fees...!

I have my own room too... but I might prefer... spending
time here with everyone...

...As for Vega, you see. She drinks a lot of water while
studying... so she ends up going to the bathroom... quite
frequently...

When I look at the flames, my heart becomes calm... The
flames here are the most comforting.
